Paper: hep-th/0005236

Date: 2000-05-25

Title: Anisotropic Four-Dimensional NS-NS String Cosmology

Authors: Chiang-Mei Chen, T. Harko and M. K. Mak

Comments: Revtex, 5 pages, 3 figures

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D63 (2001) 064002

An anisotropic (Bianchi type I) cosmology is considered in thefour-dimensional NS-NS sector of low-energy effective string theory coupled toa dilaton and an axion-like $H$-field within a de Sitter-Einstein framebackground. The time evolution of this Universe is discussed in both theEinstein and string frames.